  "answer": "The matla (opening couplet) of Ghalib's ghazal does not directly address separation until Judgment Day. However, the thematic radif couplet in the same ghazal (Diwan-E-Ghalib, ch. 3) does:\n\n> This separation lasts till judgment's dawn;  \n> For me, a week is heavy, till the morning's light.[^1]\n\n[^1]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, ch. 3 (\"Aah ko chahiye ik umr asar hote tak\"), [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/03-aah-ko-chahiye-ik-umr-asar-hote-tak/translation/#p-1ec337).",
